are applied to a variety of models of multivariate modulated Markov price processes. The principal novelty of presented results is based on consideration of multivariate modulated Markov price processes and general pay-off functions, which can depend not only on price but also an additional stochastic modulating index component, and use of minimal conditions of smoothness for transition probabilities and pay-off functions, compactness conditions for log-price processes and rate of growth conditions for pay-off functions. The volume presents results on structural studies of optimal stopping domains, Monte Carlo based approximation reward algorithms, and convergence of American-type options for autoregressive and continuous time models, as well as results of the corresponding experimental studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican option, Optimal stopping, Convergence of rewards, Markov chain, Approximation algorithm.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematics eBook-Packagez978311049493808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics, Physics 2014z9783110370355oZDB-23-DEM0 cEPUBz97831103899060 cprintz978311032968140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311032984140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110329841423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110329841.jpg  a978-3-11-049493-8  DG Studies in Mathematics eBook-Package  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_ECL_MTPY